  "abstract": "Amischophacelus axillaris is a common problem weed of Kharif in this\r\narea and has been reported from Andhra Pradesh, Maharashtra and Uttar Pradesh\r\n(Joshi 1974). The general practice is the hand removal. As the chemical control\r\nhas been reported (Dubey and Mall 1972, Lall and Choudhary 1974, Amritphale\r\n1976) for many weeds with vegetative propagation an attempt for the chemical\r\ncontrol of this weed has been made....\r\n",
